  "riddle": "1. Seek the sounds of a timeless record called \"Life Among the Ruins.\" In what year was this musical journey released?\n\n2. There exists a page where the binding of music and art flourished from 1964 to 1966. What years frame this significant wave of creativity?\n\n3. In the tapestry of these years, count how many libraries exist nearby this transformative era. \n\n4. Your discovery lies in numbers; find how many 1-bits are present in the binary form of the answer from clue 3.\n\n5. Moving forward, track down what device revolutionized music playback with its unique tape format, and how many parallel tracks does it have?\n\n6. Reflect on the answer from clue 5; what's the sum of its distinct prime factors? \n\n7. Uncover the studio that once served as a creative haven for artists. Where is the headquarters of this revered place situated?\n\n8. While traversing new landscapes, how high does the ground of Suffern, New York, rise above the sea?\n\n9. Within reach of Suffern, search for the number of stadiums standing proudly in its vicinity.\n\n10. Combine your findings from clues 8 and 9 to uncover a new total: what do you get when you add the elevation found to the number of local stadiums?\n\n11. What is the count of churches that grace the grounds near the vibrant city of Montreal? \n\n12. Engage with the world of music packaging; how many pieces comprise the iconic structure that holds CDs within its folds?\n\n13. For your grand finale, calculate the digital root of the total formed by adding the figure from clue 1, clue 9, clue 10, and clue 11 together. What single-digit revelation awaits you?",
